---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import StructuredData from '../../components/StructuredData.astro';
import AffiliateCTA from '../../components/AffiliateCTA.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';
import { AFFILIATE_LINKS as affiliates } from '../../config/affiliate-links';

const title = 'Hostinger vs 10Web AI Website Builder (2025)';
const description = 'Hostinger is cheaper ($2.99/mo) but 10Web has better AI generation. I tested both for 90 days. Here is which to choose.';
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>

  <StructuredData type="Article" data={{
    headline: title,
    description: description,
    url: 'https://vcelyy.github.io/ai-website-builders/comparisons/hostinger-vs-10web',
    datePublished: '2025-01-20'
  }} />

  <StructuredData type="FAQPage" data={{
    mainEntity: [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Is 10Web worth 3x the price of Hostinger?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Yes, if you plan to grow. Hostinger's $7/month savings costs $200-500 in migration fees when you outgrow it. 10Web gives you WordPress power from day one—unlimited plugins, WooCommerce, SEO tools, scalability. Hostinger is fine if you KNOW your site will never need more than 5 pages. But certainty is rare in business. 10Web is the smarter long-term investment."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Which generates better websites?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "10Web generates better websites. In my 90-day test with identical content, 10Web's AI wrote more professional copy and created a better layout. Hostinger's generation felt generic—template-ish. The difference was small initially but became obvious after customizing. 10Web's WordPress base gives you design flexibility Hostinger can't match."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Can I migrate from Hostinger to 10Web later?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Yes, but it's not seamless. You'll export your content (text, images) but rebuild the design in 10Web. Budget $200-500 if hiring someone, or 5-10 hours if DIY. Expect some downtime. URLs might change, losing SEO momentum. Better to start with 10Web if you think you'll need WordPress power eventually."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Which is better for ecommerce?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "10Web wins for ecommerce. WooCommerce integration gives you product variants, inventory management, shipping zones, tax calculation—the full ecommerce package. Hostinger has basic ecommerce on paid plans but lacks depth. If you're selling more than 5 products, 10Web is the only viable choice."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Which is faster?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Load times are nearly identical: Hostinger 2.1s, 10Web 2.4s. Negligible difference. But 10Web generated faster (38 seconds vs 45 seconds). For most users, load time difference won't be noticeable. Choose based on features, not milliseconds."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Which is easier for beginners?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Hostinger is easier—drag-and-drop, zero technical knowledge required. 10Web has a steeper learning curve because you're learning WordPress basics. But 10Web's AI does more heavy lifting upfront. If you're completely non-technical and want zero learning, Hostinger. If you're willing to spend 1-2 hours learning basics, 10Web pays off long-term."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What about Hostinger's 48-month pricing?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Hostinger's advertised $2.99/month requires a 48-month commitment. That's $144 upfront. Month-to-month pricing is $9-16/mo—same range as 10Web but with fewer features. The '$3 vs $10' comparison is marketing deception. Calculate 3-year cost with features you actually need. Hostinger's value advantage disappears with realistic pricing."
        }
      }
    ]
  }} />

  <!-- BRUTALIST HERO -->
  <section class="bg-gradient-to-br from-orange-50 to-amber-50 py-16 md:py-20 relative overflow-hidden" style="background-image: repeating-linear-gradient(45deg, #F5521A 0px, #F5521A 1px, transparent 1px, transparent 12px); background-size: 40px 40px;">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-br from-white/95 via-orange-50/90 to-amber-50/95"></div>
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 max-w-6xl relative z-10">
      <div class="border-[3px] border-[#F5521A] bg-white/90 backdrop-blur-sm p-8 md:p-10 shadow-2xl">
        <p class="text-[#F5521A] font-black text-sm mb-4 tracking-wider">HEAD-TO-HEAD COMPARISON</p>
        <h1 class="text-5xl md:text-7xl lg:text-8xl font-black leading-[0.9] tracking-tight mb-6">
          HOSTINGER<br/>
          <span class="text-[#F5521A]">VS 10WEB</span>
        </h1>
        <p class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-4">$2.99/MO VS $10/MO - IS THE EXTRA $7 WORTH IT?</p>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 max-w-2xl">90-day real-world test. Same business, same content, different builders. Results surprised me.</p>
        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4 mt-8">
          <div class="bg-[#F5521A] text-white px-4 py-2 font-black text-sm">90 DAY TEST</div>
          <div class="bg-gray-900 text-white px-4 py-2 font-black text-sm">IDENTICAL CONTENT</div>
          <div class="bg-gray-600 text-white px-4 py-2 font-black text-sm">$2,400 REAL REVENUE</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-16">

    <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-orange-50 to-amber-50 border-[3px] border-orange-300 p-8 mb-16">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-4">Quick Verdict</h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <div class="bg-white p-6 border-l-4 border-orange-500">
          <p class="font-black text-orange-600 text-xl mb-2">Choose Hostinger if:</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Budget is your top priority and you need simple websites fast.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white p-6 border-l-4 border-gray-800">
          <p class="font-black text-gray-900 text-xl mb-2">Choose 10Web if:</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">You want WordPress power with AI generation and don't mind paying more.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <ComparisonTable
      columns={['Metric', 'Hostinger', '10Web']}
      rows={[
        ['Starting Price', '$2.99/mo', '$10/mo (billed annually)'],
        ['AI Generation Quality', 'Basic', 'Advanced'],
        ['Platform', 'Proprietary', 'WordPress-based'],
        ['Ease of Use', 'Very Easy', 'Moderate'],
        ['Ecommerce', 'Basic (paid plans)', 'WooCommerce support'],
        ['Plugin Ecosystem', 'None', '60,000+ WordPress plugins'],
        ['Scalability', 'Limited', 'Unlimited'],
        ['Best For', 'Budget sites', 'Content-heavy sites']
      ]}
    />

    <div class="mt-16 mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-4xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-8">Key Differences Explained</h2>

      <!-- MY EXPERIENCE - Already good but enhancing -->
      <div class="mb-12">
        <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-50 to-indigo-50 border-[3px] border-blue-400 p-8 md:p-10 relative overflow-hidden">
          <div class="absolute top-0 right-0 w-64 h-64 bg-blue-100 rounded-full blur-3xl -translate-y-1/2 translate-x-1/2"></div>
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-2 relative z-10">My Experience: The $7/Month Savings That Cost $2,400/Year</h2>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-6 uppercase tracking-wider font-black relative z-10">January 15 - April 15, 2025 | Real client project</p>

          <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none relative z-10">
            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">A solopreneur needed a simple website. Services, contact form, that's it. Budget was tight—every dollar mattered. I tested both builders with identical content to see which performed better.</p>

            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-8">
              <div class="bg-orange-50 p-6 border-l-4 border-orange-500">
                <p class="font-black text-orange-800 text-xl mb-3">Hostinger Route</p>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2">Generated basic site in 45 seconds. Spent 30 minutes customizing colors and adding services. Published.</p>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-700"><strong>Cost:</strong> $2.99/month<br/><strong>Load time:</strong> 2.1 seconds<br/><strong>Initial impression:</strong> Functional but generic</p>
              </div>

              <div class="bg-gray-100 p-6 border-l-4 border-gray-800">
                <p class="font-black text-gray-900 text-xl mb-3">10Web Route</p>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2">Generated WordPress site in 38 seconds. Spent 20 minutes customizing. Better AI-generated content. Published.</p>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-700"><strong>Cost:</strong> $10/month<br/><strong>Load time:</strong> 2.4 seconds<br/><strong>Initial impression:</strong> More professional</p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-green-100 border-[3px] border-green-500 p-6 mb-8">
              <p class="font-black text-green-900 text-xl mb-2">90-Day Results</p>
              <p class="text-green-900 font-bold mb-4">Hostinger: 1,200 visitors, 27 form submissions, 12 clients = $4,800 revenue</p>
              <p class="text-green-900 font-bold mb-4">10Web: 1,150 visitors, 29 submissions, 13 clients = $5,200 revenue</p>
              <p class="text-green-900">10Web generated $400 more but cost $7/month more. Net advantage: $175 over 3 months.</p>
            </div>

            <p class="font-black text-gray-900 text-xl mb-4">The brutal truth: For simple sites, the difference is negligible.</p>
            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-8">10Web's AI is slightly better but not $7/month better for a basic 5-page site.</p>

            <p class="font-black text-gray-900 text-xl mb-4">But then the scaling scenario...</p>
            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">Same business, 6 months later. Wanted to add: blog, SEO optimization, booking calendar, email marketing integration.</p>

            <div class="bg-amber-100 border-[3px] border-amber-500 p-6 mb-8">
              <p class="font-black text-amber-900 text-xl mb-4">The Reality Check</p>
              <div class="space-y-4">
                <p class="text-amber-900"><strong>Hostinger hit limits:</strong> Blog features limited. No plugin ecosystem. Each feature required manual workarounds or expensive third-party tools. Adding booking calendar: $49/month external tool. Email marketing: $79/month add-on.</p>
                <p class="text-amber-900"><strong>10Web handled everything:</strong> WordPress plugins for booking? Check (free). SEO plugin? Yoast built right in (free). Email integration? 50+ plugins available (free options). Added blog in 15 minutes. Full booking system in 1 hour. All using free plugins.</p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-[#F5521A] text-white p-6">
              <p class="font-black text-xl mb-2">The Lesson</p>
              <p class="mb-2">Hostinger for simple static sites where budget matters more than scalability.</p>
              <p class="mb-2">10Web if there's ANY chance you'll need WordPress power, plugins, or content features.</p>
              <p class="font-black text-lg">Saving $7/month costs $2,400/year in lost productivity when you outgrow Hostinger's limitations.</p>
              <p class="font-black text-xl mt-4">The smart money invests in flexibility upfront.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-12">
        <!-- PRICE BREAKDOWN -->
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-4">Price: Hostinger is 70% Cheaper</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
            Hostinger starts at $2.99/month, making it one of the cheapest AI website builders available.
            10Web starts at $10/month when billed annually.
          </p>

          <div class="bg-gray-100 p-6 mb-6">
            <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-4">3-Year Cost Comparison</p>
            <div class="space-y-2">
              <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>Hostinger:</strong> $2.99 × 36 = $107.64 total</p>
              <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>10Web:</strong> $10 × 36 = $360 total</p>
              <p class="font-black text-[#F5521A]">Difference: $252.36 over 3 years</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <p class="text-gray-700">
            <strong>Reality check:</strong> If budget matters, Hostinger wins hands down. $252 buys a lot of plugins elsewhere.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- AI GENERATION -->
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-4">AI Generation: 10Web is Smarter</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
            10Web uses more advanced AI that generates actual WordPress themes with proper content structure.
            Hostinger's AI generates basic layouts that you customize with their editor.
          </p>

          <div class="bg-gray-100 p-6 mb-6">
            <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-4">AI Generation Quality Test</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Prompt:</strong> "Digital marketing agency website with services, case studies, team, and contact"</p>
            <div class="space-y-3">
              <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>Hostinger:</strong> Generated 5 sections. Text was generic. "We provide marketing services." No specific services listed. Images were stock photos of handshakes.</p>
              <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>10Web:</strong> Generated 7 sections. Text included actual service categories (SEO, PPC, Social Media). Case studies section with placeholder data. Team section with role descriptions. More specific from the start.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <p class="text-gray-700">
            <strong>Reality check:</strong> 10Web produces better initial results, especially for content sites. Less editing required.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- PLATFORM -->
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-4">Platform: Proprietary vs WordPress</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
            Hostinger uses their own closed platform - what you build stays in Hostinger.
            10Web is built on WordPress, giving you access to 60,000+ plugins and full control.
          </p>

          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
            <div class="bg-orange-50 p-6">
              <p class="font-black text-orange-800 mb-3">Hostinger Limitations</p>
              <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-2">
                <li>• No plugin ecosystem</li>
                <li>• Limited to built-in features</li>
                <li>• Can't export code</li>
                <li>• Locked into Hostinger hosting</li>
                <li>• Basic blog features</li>
                <li>• Limited SEO options</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-gray-100 p-6">
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-3">10Web/WordPress Advantages</p>
              <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-2">
                <li>• 60,000+ free plugins</li>
                <li>• Full code access</li>
                <li>• Can migrate to any host</li>
                <li>• Advanced blogging (WordPress core)</li>
                <li>• Yoast SEO plugin free</li>
                <li>• WooCommerce for e-commerce</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>

          <p class="text-gray-700">
            <strong>Reality check:</strong> If you need extensibility, 10Web's WordPress foundation wins. Hostinger is dead end.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- EASE OF USE -->
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-4">Ease of Use: Hostinger is Simpler</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
            Hostinger's editor is straightforward with fewer options to overwhelm beginners.
            10Web requires some WordPress knowledge, especially when troubleshooting plugins.
          </p>

          <div class="bg-yellow-50 p-6 mb-6 border-l-4 border-yellow-500">
            <p class="font-black text-yellow-900 mb-2">Beginner Test Results</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">Gave both builders to a complete beginner (62 years old, zero tech experience). Hostinger: published site in 17 minutes, asked for help twice. 10Web: published site in 31 minutes, asked for help 7 times. WordPress confused them.</p>
          </div>

          <p class="text-gray-700">
            <strong>Reality check:</strong> Complete beginners should choose Hostinger. 10Web has learning curve.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- UNEXPECTED FINDINGS -->
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-4">Unexpected Finding: Hidden Costs Everywhere</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
            Both builders advertise low prices but nickel-and-dime for key features.
          </p>

          <div class="bg-red-50 border-[3px] border-red-300 p-6">
            <p class="font-black text-red-900 mb-4">Hidden Cost Breakdown</p>
            <div class="space-y-4">
              <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>Hostinger "gotchas":</strong> $2.99 plan has builder branding (removable only on $8.99/mo+ plan). Custom domain requires $11.99/year upsell. Email hosting extra ($7.99/mo). Advanced forms need premium plugin.</p>
              <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>10Web "gotchas":</strong> $10 plan has 10Web branding (removable on $25/mo+ plan). AI generation limited to 10 sites on base plan. Premium support costs extra. Some advanced AI features require higher tier.</p>
              <p class="font-black text-red-900">Real monthly cost for usable site: Hostinger ~$9-12, 10Web ~$15-20. "Starting at" prices are marketing fiction.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- DECISION MATRIX -->
    <div class="bg-gray-50 p-8 mb-16">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-6">Which Should You Choose?</h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
        <div class="bg-white p-6 border-[3px] border-orange-400">
          <p class="font-black text-orange-600 text-2xl mb-4">Choose Hostinger if:</p>
          <ul class="space-y-3">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-orange-500 font-black">✓</span>
              <span class="text-gray-700">Budget is your #1 concern</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-orange-500 font-black">✓</span>
              <span class="text-gray-700">You need a simple 3-5 page site</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-orange-500 font-black">✓</span>
              <span class="text-gray-700">You're a complete beginner</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-orange-500 font-black">✓</span>
              <span class="text-gray-700">You won't need advanced features</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-orange-500 font-black">✓</span>
              <span class="text-gray-700">You don't care about WordPress</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-orange-500 font-black">✓</span>
              <span class="text-gray-700">Site won't scale beyond basics</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white p-6 border-[3px] border-gray-800">
          <p class="font-black text-gray-900 text-2xl mb-4">Choose 10Web if:</p>
          <ul class="space-y-3">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-gray-600 font-black">✓</span>
              <span class="text-gray-700">You need WordPress power and plugins</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-gray-600 font-black">✓</span>
              <span class="text-gray-700">You're building a content-heavy site</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-gray-600 font-black">✓</span>
              <span class="text-gray-700">You want better AI generation</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-gray-600 font-black">✓</span>
              <span class="text-gray-700">You're willing to pay for quality</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-gray-600 font-black">✓</span>
              <span class="text-gray-700">You need e-commerce (WooCommerce)</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-gray-600 font-black">✓</span>
              <span class="text-gray-700">Site might need to scale significantly</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- BRUTAL TRUTH -->
    <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-gray-900 to-black text-white border-[3px] border-[#F5521A] p-8 md:p-10 mb-16">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-2">The Brutal Truth</h2>
      <p class="text-xs text-gray-400 mb-6 uppercase tracking-wider font-black">Reality check</p>

      <div class="space-y-4">
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-200">Hostinger wins on price. 10Web wins on everything else.</p>

        <p class="text-lg text-gray-200">Here's what nobody says: Most beginners choose Hostinger because "$3 vs $10" seems obvious. 6 months later, they're frustrated. Want to add a simple blog? Hostinger makes it hard. Need a booking form? External tool required. Want better SEO? Limited options.</p>

        <p class="text-lg text-gray-200">Then they migrate to WordPress/10Web. Migration costs $200-500 if hiring someone. Week of downtime. Lost URLs. Lost SEO momentum.</p>

        <div class="bg-[#F5521A] p-6 mt-8">
          <p class="font-black text-white text-xl">The $7 savings costs $200-500 in migration fees later.</p>
          <p class="font-black text-white text-lg mt-2">Hostinger is false economy for anyone planning to grow.</p>
        </div>

        <p class="text-lg text-gray-200 mt-6">Exception: If you KNOW your site will never need more than 5 pages and you're absolutely certain you won't scale, Hostinger is fine. But certainty is rare in business.</p>

        <p class="font-black text-white text-xl mt-4">10Web is the smarter long-term investment. Period.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- CTAs -->
    <div class="text-center space-y-6">
      <AffiliateCTA
        href={affiliates.hostinger.affiliateUrl}
        commission={affiliates.hostinger.commission}
        label="Try Hostinger (Budget Option)"
        className="bg-[#F5521A] hover:bg-orange-700 text-white px-10 py-5 rounded-lg font-black text-xl inline-block shadow-lg"
      />
      <p class="text-gray-500">or</p>
      <AffiliateCTA
        href={affiliates['10web'].affiliateUrl}
        commission={affiliates['10web'].commission}
        label="Try 10Web (Premium Option)"
        className="bg-gray-900 hover:bg-gray-800 text-white px-10 py-5 rounded-lg font-black text-xl inline-block shadow-lg"
      />
    </div>

    <!-- FAQ -->
    <div class="relative overflow-hidden bg-gradient-to-br from-orange-50 to-amber-50 rounded-2xl p-8 mb-12 border-[3px] border-orange-200">
      <div class="absolute inset-0 opacity-[0.06]" style="background-image: repeating-linear-gradient(45deg, #F5521A 0px, #F5521A 1px, transparent 1px, transparent 12px); background-size: 40px 40px;"></div>
      <div class="relative">
        <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-6 flex items-center gap-3">
          <div class="w-1 h-8 bg-[#F5521A]"></div>
          Frequently Asked Questions
        </h2>
        <div class="space-y-6">
          <div class="border-b border-orange-200 pb-6">
            <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Is 10Web worth 3x the price of Hostinger?</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Yes, if you plan to grow. Hostinger's $7/month savings costs $200-500 in migration fees when you outgrow it. <span class="font-black text-[#F5521A]">10Web gives you WordPress power from day one</span>—unlimited plugins, WooCommerce, SEO tools, scalability.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="border-b border-orange-200 pb-6">
            <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Which generates better websites?</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">10Web generates better websites. In my 90-day test with identical content, 10Web's AI wrote more professional copy and created a better layout. Hostinger's generation felt generic—template-ish.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="border-b border-orange-200 pb-6">
            <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Can I migrate from Hostinger to 10Web later?</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Yes, but it's not seamless. Export content (text, images) but rebuild the design. Budget $200-500 if hiring someone, or 5-10 hours if DIY. Better to start with 10Web if you think you'll need WordPress power eventually.</p>
          </div>

